text.section:
This subtitle does not apply to:
Prepackaged food which contains separately identifiable items that are separated by physical division within the package;
Any item sold only by prescription;
Any item subject to the packaging or labeling requirements of the Federal Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco and Firearms or to any pricing requirements under federal law;
Any item actually being sold through a vending machine;
Any item delivered directly to a retail sales agency without passing through warehousing or other inventory facility used by the agency; or
Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, a retail sales agency which:
During the preceding calendar year, sold a gross volume of consumer commodities of less than $750,000;
Is not part of a company which consists of ten or more sales agencies in or out of the State;
Derives less than 15 percent of its total revenues from consumer commodities subject to this subtitle; or
Is owned and operated by not more than one individual and the members of his immediate family.
